TOM Website Privacy Policy
Innovation 6 AG, Pfäffikerstrasse 109, 8615 Wermatswil, Switzerland, registered in the commercial register of the
canton of Zurich under number CHE-263.807.653 (
Innovation 6
or
we
) is the
operator
of the website www.tommedications.com (
website
) and also provides the medication management app
TOM
(
TOM
). Innovation 6 is the controller for the processing of your personal data through the
website
and TOM.
Innovation 6 places great importance on the appropriate handling of the personal data of the user of our website
and
TOM (the
user
or
you
). Naturally, where relevant, we comply with the legal
requirements of the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP), the Swiss Ordinance on Data Protection (DPO),
the
EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and any other applicable data protection provisions. Due to the
wider
geographical application, the terms of the GDPR are used below. In particular, the German terms
‘
Bearbeitung
’ of ‘
Personendaten
’ used in the FADP are replaced by the terms
‘
Verarbeitung
’ of ‘
personenbezogene Daten
’ in the GDPR (in both instances these translate to
‘processing’ of ‘personal data’ in English) and ‘
überwigendes Interesse
’ (‘overriding interest’) is
replaced by ‘
berechtiges Interesse
’ (‘legitimate interest’). However, the legal meaning of the terms is
still determined in accordance with the FADP in the context of the application of the FADP.
Below you will find details on the nature, scope and purpose of our processing of your personal data when you
visit
our website. You can find the TOM privacy policy here
https://www.tommedications.com/datenschutzerklaerung#en
.
Please note that the following information may be amended from time to time by publishing an updated version of
this
privacy policy. This privacy policy was last amended on 23 November 2023.
1. Data collected, purpose of the collection and use of the data
1.1 Data collected automatically when you visit our website
When you visit our website, the following data is automatically collected:
data on network connections and website activity (e.g. IP address, name and URL of the requested file, host name
of the accessing computer, date and time of access)
device information for the device used (e.g. manufacturer, model, platform, operating system)
region or language settings
The processing of this data is required for the use of our website for technical reasons. In particular, it
guarantees the orderly operation and optimisation of the functionality and display quality of the website. This
data
is also used for internal statistical evaluation of user behaviour. This processing is required to safeguard the
legitimate interests of Innovation 6 (legal basis: Art. 6[1][f] GDPR).
1.2 Cookies
We also use cookies to make your visit to our website easier and more pleasant (see also section ‎1.6). Cookies
are
text files that your web browser automatically stores on your device when you visit our website. The session
cookies
used are deleted after each visit to our website, while persistent cookies are stored for a defined period after
the
end of the browser session and used to recognise returning users. If this is required under law, we obtain your
prior consent for the use of cookies (legal basis: Art. 6[1][a] and [f] GDPR).
You can prevent cookies from being stored on your device by configuring your web browser accordingly. However, if
you
disable all cookies, you may be unable to use some of the features of our website.
We use the following cookies on our website:
_ga
Cookie provider: Google Analytics
Lifespan: 2 years
Function: Google Analytics sets this cookie to uniquely identify users.
_gid
Cookie provider: Google Analytics
Lifespan: 24 hours
Function: Google Analytics sets this cookie to uniquely identify users.
_gat
Cookie provider: Google Analytics
Lifespan: 1 minute
Function: limiting the number of requests to Google servers within a certain period of time.
wp-wpml_current_language
Cookie provider: tom medications
Lifespan: 1 day
Function: storing the language setting.
VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE
Cookie provider: YouTube
Lifespan: 6 months
Function: enabling ad placement or retargeting to store and track a visitor’s identity and interactions.
YSC
Cookie provider: YouTube
Lifespan: session
Function: storing and tracking interactions.
511
Cookie provider: Google
Lifespan: 6 months
Function: authentication service.
AEC
Cookie provider: Google
Lifespan: 6 months
Function: ensuring that requests within a browser session are made by the user and not by other websites.
SOCS
Cookie provider: Google
Lifespan: 30 days
Function: storing cookie decisions.
CONSENT
Cookie provider: Google
Lifespan: 1 year
Function: storing cookie decisions.
c
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 6 months
Function: authentication and tracking.
bcookie
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 1 year
Function: browser identification cookie used for diagnostic purposes.
li_sugr
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 3 months
Function: identifying probabilistic similarities of the identity of a user outside the designated countries.
AnalyticsSyncHistory
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 1 month
Function: recording when there has been synchronisation with the cookie ‘lms_analytics’.
UserMatchHistory
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 1 month
Function: synchronising the IDs of LinkedIn ads.
lidc
Cookie provider: LinkedIn
Lifespan: 1 day
Function: selecting the data centre.
1.3. Use of the contact form
If you contact us using the contact form on our website, we collect the following data:
First and last name (company email)
Email
Telephone number
Your message
We use this data to process and respond to your query (legal basis: Art. 6[1][a] GDPR).
1.4. Medication entry option
On our website you have the option of recording your medication plan as well as the daily dosage and timing of
these
medications. To help you, there are various country-specific medication databases to make it easier to identify
medications. In determining which database to access and/or the relevant country, the region and language
settings
of your mobile device are used and, in the event of problems, the IP address (legal basis: Art. 6[1][b] GDPR).
You can transmit the information you collect to TOM by using TOM to scan the QR code displayed on the website in
which your information is digitally encoded. The QR code does not include a tracking mechanism. If you are not
yet
using TOM, you will need to install TOM on your mobile device first. For information on the collection and use
of
your data in TOM, please refer to the TOM privacy policy.
https://www.tommedications.com/datenschutzerklaerung#en
Once the information has been transferred to TOM or if you decide not to transfer the information entered to TOM,
both the information and the QR code are deleted from the website. This information is not stored or archived on
our
website.
1.5. Clicking on embedded external links
Through the external links embedded on our website, you will be redirected to the websites of third parties (e.g.
Google Play Store, Apple App Store, social networks, instant messaging services such as WhatsApp and Telegram).
Innovation 6 has no influence on, nor is it responsible for, the data collected and the data processing
operations
of these third parties. Please refer to the website in question to find out how it handles your data.
1.6. Analytics tool
Our website uses the analytics service Google Analytics (GA4). Analysis of the use of our website helps stabilise
and
improve our website and to generate crash reports. We use the analytics services to safeguard our legitimate
interest in the best possible provision of our website (legal basis: Art. 6[1][f] GDPR).
This analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Ireland and Google LLC, USA (collectively
Google
) uses cookies or other identifiers that are stored on your device and that collect data
about your use of our website (e.g. IP address/ID number, time and duration of use, location, device, return or
new
visit, time stamp of crash). In this context, pseudonymised user profiles are created. You can find more
information
on the data collected here:
https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245?hl=en
.
You can prevent the storage of cookies by selecting the appropriate settings on your web browser. However, if
you
disable all cookies, you may be unable to use some of the features of our website.
The data collected in connection with your use of our website may also be transmitted to a Google server in the
USA
and stored there. As the ‘IP anonymisation’ function is activated for our website, before transmission Google
will
truncate your IP address within the member states of the European Union or other signatory states to the
Agreement
on the European Economic Area or Switzerland. Only in exceptional cases is the complete IP address transmitted
to a
Google server in the US and truncated there. Google does not combine the IP address transmitted by your device
with
other data. Google is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework and the Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework.
You
can find more information here:
www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/
.
If you do not want Google to use your data, you can use the following browser add-on to deactivate Google:
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=en
.
1.7. Video content
We use YouTube to play videos. This usage safeguards our legitimate interest in the best possible provision of
our
website (legal basis: Art. 6[1][f] GDPR).
Video content is provided by YouTube LLC, USA, a subsidiary of Google. Google Ireland Limited is responsible for
all
data processing in Europe. If you visit a page on our website that has a YouTube video embedded in it, your
browser
automatically connects to the servers of YouTube or Google, which may be located in the USA. YouTube sets at
least
one cookie that stores your IP address and our URL. If you are logged in to your YouTube account, YouTube can
use
cookies to assign your interactions on our website to your profile. YouTube processes various forms of
additional
data. We have no control over the scope, use and duration of storage with respect to data collected by Google.
Google is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework and the Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework. You can find
more information on data protection at:
https://policies.google.com/privacy
;
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=en
and
https://adssettings.google.com/authenticated
.
2. Social media platforms
We maintain an online presence in various social networks to communicate with interested parties and users active
there and to inform them about Innovation 6 and TOM (legal basis: Art. 6[1][f] GDPR).
On our website we have embedded links to our online presence in the following social networks:
Facebook
Instagram
LinkedIn
YouTube
When you click on the relevant icons, you will be automatically redirected to our profile on the platform in
question. A direct connection is established between your web browser and the servers of the platform in
question,
which may be located in a third country (e.g. the USA). The platform receives the information that you have
visited
our website with your IP address and accessed the link. When you click on such a link while you are logged into
your
account with the relevant platform, the content of our site may be linked to your profile on the platform, which
means that the platform can directly associate your visit to our website with your user account. If you wish to
prevent this, log out before you click on the relevant link. Allocation will definitely take place if you log in
to
the relevant platform after clicking on the link.
Please note that you use our Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn and YouTube pages and their functions under your own
responsibility. This applies in particular to the use of interactive functions (e.g. comment, share, rate).
During
this use, personal data is collected by the relevant networks and may be transmitted to countries outside
Switzerland and the European Union and processed there.
We do not know what information Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn and YouTube collect and process. For a detailed
description of the respective processing operations and options for opting out, please refer to the following
linked
information of these providers.
Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/
https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=ads
Instagram:
https://privacycenter.instagram.com/policy/
LinkedIn:
https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy
https://www.linkedin.com/psettings/guest-controls
YouTube:
https://policies.google.com/privacy
https://www.youtube.com/t/terms
3. Hosting and maintenance
The data collected is transferred to the cloud server of our hosting service provider dogado GmbH, in Germany,
and
stored there in Innovation 6 databases. dogado GmbH, in Germany, and the IT company bitsfabrik GmbH, in Austria,
which is responsible for the development and maintenance of the website, have access to this data in connection
with
the provision of their services. The service providers only access this data in association with the operation
and
maintenance of the server, and the maintenance, troubleshooting and ongoing development of our website. We use
these
services to safeguard our legitimate interest in the best possible provision of our website (legal basis: Art.
6[1][f] GDPR).
4. Transmission of data abroad
As mentioned in this privacy policy (see sections 1.6 and 3), data is transferred to persons and/or companies
abroad.
Naturally the statutory provisions on disclosure of personal data to third parties are observed in this
transfer.
Some of the countries to which data is transferred have an adequate level of data protection as decided by the
Federal Council (FADP) and the European Commission (GDPR) (e.g. member states of the EEA, Switzerland), while
other
countries (e.g. the USA) have a level of data protection assessed as inadequate. If the country concerned does
not
have an adequate level of data protection and if there is no explicit consent from the user, transmission is not
required by contract or law and there is no other applicable exemption provision (Art. 49 GDPR), we conclude
contracts with the standard data protection clauses provided by the European Commission and Switzerland’s
Federal
Data Protection and Information Commissioner (
FDPIC
), which provide guarantees for the
protection
of your data at the service provider or recipient in the third country.
Information on data transfer to the USA:
Based on the EU-US Data Privacy Framework agreed with the USA
and
the Executive Order issued by the President of the USA on 7 October 2022, the European Commission has determined
in
an adequacy decision that the USA ensures an adequate level of protection for personal data. However, this only
applies to US companies that are certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework and thus undertake to comply
with
its provisions. You can find information on whether a US service provider we have engaged is certified under the
EU-US Data Privacy Framework in this privacy policy. You can find the list of all certified US companies and
more
information on the EU-US Data Privacy Framework on the US Department of Commerce website at
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov. Negotiations between Switzerland and the USA in connection with the
Swiss-US
Data Privacy Framework and recognition of the adequacy of the level of data protection are ongoing. The decision
of
the Federal Council is still pending.
5. Data storage period
All personal data that we collect during your visit to our website or that you transfer to us is deleted as soon
as
it is no longer required for the purpose for which it was processed (see also section ‎1.2 and section ‎1.4) and
if
its retention is not required by law.
6. Data security
We take appropriate technical and organisational security precautions to protect your personal data from
unauthorised
access and misuse. In connection with subcontractors used to provide our services, we also take appropriate
legal
precautions to ensure the protection of your personal data in line with the relevant statutory provisions.
7. Data protection rights
Within the context of the data protection legislation applicable to you and where provided for therein, you may
request information on your data stored by us
, and you have the
right to receive your
data
in a commonly used machine-readable format
. In justified cases, you may also request the
erasure or correction of your data
or the
restriction of its processing
,
or object to the processing of your data
or
withdraw your consent to
processing
.
You also have the right to
lodge a complaint with the responsible supervisory authority
.
Please note that we reserve the right to assert our legally mandated right to impose restrictions, for instance
if we
are obliged to retain or process certain data or have an overriding interest in it.
